page.title: 17A West Indian Church.
page.content: My name is Debbie Elliot. Well I go down to church on Saturday at 8.am and come back 12 pm I sit down and get ready to sing. First,I have to read a story about God. I enjoy it. After I have read I listen to everyone else. Then we sing about God and we kiss the cross. After, we have Jamaican food, fruit pie, it has mangoes and apple and coconut and pastry, Jamaican dumplings and stew, Jamaican corn is chicken and rice and kidney beans.Then I go home.At half past nine I go to bed on school day. Before I get into bed I say my prayers and say what I did. Then I read a story about God and then I go to sleep.
